public abstract class ResourceLoader<E extends ResourceLoader.Entry,R>
extends Object
implements Iterable<Integer>

An abstract class for loading resources by a unique identifier.

Resource Meta-Information
Each implementation has a nested class that must extend Entry; which describes the meta-information about a resource. The meta information is loaded separately from the resource to reduce memory usage and provide a way to inspect the resource before it's loaded.

Performance Guidelines
The ResourceLoader abstraction attempts to provide a solid framework for accessing resources effecently from a data source. Any resources returned by the implemented get(int) method should remain valid, but may still access the data source. To conserve memory implementations should allow the garbage collector to determine when a loaded resouce is no longer used; and re-load resources dynamically when requested.

Iterability
An iterator is provided for getting all of the valid identifiers in the data source. An iterator can be requested explicitly using the iterator() method or implicitly using a foreach loop. The ResourceLoader is not backed by the iterator and any attempts to invoke a remove will throw an exception.

Author:
Kristopher Ives, Lucas Green
